The children killed in a taxi crash outside Bronkhorstspruit have all been identified. This paves the way for the children to be buried.Sixteen learners and the General Assistant will be buried in Welvenkop in Verena on Saturday while two learners will be buried on Sunday in KwaNongoma in KwaZulu-Natal and Limpopo respectively.The funeral of the mini bus driver was held last Saturday in Welvenkop. The driver was transporting the learners when the taxi collided with a truck near Bronkhorstspruit on Friday afternoon.The Schools memorial Service will be held on Wednesday, 3 May at the Sokhulumi Village at 13:00 while the public memorial will take place on Thursday at the Verena Open Ground at 11:00.